Package Lybrinth

package Lybrinth
  • Class
    Description
    AnimatedThings
    Represents animated objects in the game world.
    CongratsScreen
    Represents the congratulations screen displayed when the player successfully finishes all the three levels.
    CustomProgressBar
    Custom progress bar class that extends JProgressBar to provide a customized visual appearance.
    Dungeon
    Represents the dungeon in the game, holding the layout, entities, and other elements.
    DynamicThings
    Represents dynamic entities in the game world that can move and interact with their environment.
    Food
    Represents food in the game, which is a type of SolidThing.
    GameOverScreen
    Represents the game over screen displayed when the player loses the game (Time's up or health down to 0).
    GameRender
    Represents the rendering component of the game, responsible for drawing the game elements.
    Hero
    The `Lybrinth.Hero` class represents the player's character in the game.
    HitBox
    Represents a hitbox used for collision detection.
    MainInterface
    Main interface for the game, providing the primary window for gameplay.
    Orientation
    Enumerates the possible orientations for entities in the game.
    SolidThings
    Represents a solid object in the game.
    TestHero
    Test class for demonstrating the singleton pattern implementation in the Lybrinth.Hero class.
    TestHitBox
    Test class for demonstrating the functionality of the Lybrinth.HitBox class.
    TestMovement
    Test class for demonstrating the movement functionality of the Lybrinth.Hero class within a Lybrinth.Dungeon.
    Things
    Represents a basic object in the game.
    TileManager
    Manages tiles for rendering in the game.
    TitleScreen
    Represents the title screen of the game.
    Trap
    Represents a trap in the game, which is a type of SolidThing that can inflict damage.
